title: Pneumatic Craft Monitoring
content:
--local side =peripheral.getNames()
local pneu = peripheral.wrap("back")
local mon = peripheral.wrap("top")
mode = "auto"

function Anzeige()
    mon.setTextColor(colors.white)
    mon.clear()
    mon.setCursorPos(1,1)
    mon.write("Aktueller Durck:")
    mon.setCursorPos(1,3)
    mon.write("Generator: ")
    mon.setTextColor(color)
    mon.setCursorPos(1,2)
    mon.write(string.format("%.2f",pressure).. "bar")
    mon.setCursorPos(12,3)
    mon.write(status)
    mon.setCursorPos(1,4)

end

function Auto()
        if pressure > 4.6 then
        rs.setOutput("right",false)
        rs.setOutput("back", false)
        color = colors.red
        status = "off"
    elseif pressure < 3.5 then
        rs.setOutput("right",true)
        rs.setOutput("back", true)
        color = colors.green
        status = "on"
    else 
        color = colors.orange   
    end
end
function Klick(x,y)
    if y== 3 and x >= 12 and x <= 15 then
        dropdownVisible = not dropdownVisible
         elseif dropdownVisible then
        if y == 4 then
            SetMode("AUTO")
        elseif y == 5 then
            SetMode("ON")
        elseif y == 6 then
            SetMode("OFF")
        else
            dropdownVisible = false
        end
    end

end

function SetMode(newMode)
    mode = newMode
    dropdownVisible = false

    if newMode == "ON" then
        rs.setOutput("right", true)
        rs.setOutput("back", true)
    elseif newMode == "OFF" then
        rs.setOutput("right", false)
        rs.setOutput("back", false)
    end
end

function Menue()
    local event, side, x, y = os.pullEventTimeout("monitor_touch", 0.5)
    if event == "monitor_touch" then
        Klick(x,y)
    end
end
while true do
pressure = pneu.getPressure()
    if mode == "AUTO" then
        Auto()
    end
Auto()
Anzeige()
sleep(0.5)
end
